# SEO and semantic markup (Al-Ameen Caps)

## Automation & maintenance (mandatory for all new work)

1. **Every new page must include a JSON-LD schema.** Use `Seo` + `src/lib/seo.js` (e.g. `getProductSchema`, `getBreadcrumbSchema`, `getLocalBusinessSchema`, `getOrganizationSchema`, `getWebSiteSchema`, `getFAQPageSchema`, Article schemas). Do not ship a public page without at least one relevant schema.
2. **Every image must have explicit dimensions and alt text.** Use `width` and `height` attributes (or CSS `aspect-ratio`) to prevent CLS. Every `<img>` must have a meaningful `alt` (empty `alt=""` only for purely decorative images).
3. **Use semantic HTML5 landmarks.** Prefer `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, `<section>`, `<header>`, `<footer>` over generic `<div>` for page structure so crawlers can map content.

## Entity-rich copy and schema

- Use explicit terms (Kufi, Taqiyah, Fez, Jumu'ah, Salah, Cape Town, Bo-Kaap, Attar, Oud, Cape Malay) in meta descriptions, schema descriptions, and visible body copy where natural. Avoid keyword stuffing.
- LocalBusiness and Organization schemas must reference Bo-Kaap heritage and Cape Malay culture where relevant.
- Product meta and Product schema use category-based entity tails (e.g. "Perfect for Jumu'ah and Eid" for Caps).

## Performance (LCP & CLS)

- Preload LCP hero image from `index.html`: `<link rel="preload" as="image" href="/hero-bg.webp" fetchpriority="high" />`.
- Use explicit aspect ratio (e.g. `aspect-[4/5]`) on product image containers to prevent layout shift.
- Fonts must use `display=swap` (already in index).

## Site URL

- Use `import.meta.env.VITE_SITE_URL` (or helpers from `src/lib/seo.js`) for canonical URLs and schema; see deployment rule for production domain.
